Nollywood actress, Emilia Dike, has died. The actress reportedly slumped and died in Enugu state on Wednesday May 20. Movie Director, Okechukwu Oku, announced her passing on his Instagram page. ”Why is death taking the best people???? I’m confused oooo. Just filmed with Mama here on my 2 last projects, excited to release it and this horrible news today. A woman with a heart of gold, Aah noooo. Will miss you Mrs Dike. Nollywood has lost a gem in you. This is messed up” he wrote. Actors, Uche Ogbodo, Anita Joseph, Belinda Effah, Ken Erics and others have expressed shock at the news of her passing. Emilia Dike featured in Nollywood movies such as Ignorant couples, Dust of yesterday, Kings Guard, Where Money Never Sleep 1 and 2, and many more. Source Nollywood actress Tonto Dikeh has made new revelations about her female colleagues in the Nigerian movie industry. The actress who was a guest on Planet TV Africa’s One on One talk show spoke about everything from her career as an actress and singer to her friendship with popular crossdresser Bobrisky.… April 26, 2019 In "Entertainment" Jolly Muke crooner, Jaywon has been spotted with Nollywood actress cum musician, Tonto Dike-Churchill in the studio. Jaywon posted a photo of their studio session which caption ‘ Oba Orin &Tonto Dike-Churchill cooking something real big; Tontolet is back in the music game for real, you all need to anticipate… July 19, 2016 In "Entertainment" Nollywood actress, Tonto Dike, has revealed why she described her estranged husband, Olakunle Churchill as a “40 seconds” man. Tonto was responding to a fan who berated her for using Churchill’s alleged sexual deficiency to publicly shame him. Tonto said she made her ex-husband’s inabilities public because he first accused… May 7, 2019 In "Entertainment"